      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical R2022 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented QA procedures including regression testing and ISO 9001 certification. FDA in-house code underwent independent verification. Required and achieved levels are equal at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems including patch tests and single-element tests were executed. Results compared against analytical solutions with relative errors below 0.5%, confirming correct implementation of element formulations used in the pedicle screw model."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed with three refinement levels. Key QoI (construct stiffness and peak von Mises stress) changed by less than 2% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI values below 3% confirm discretization error is adequately controlled."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Direct sparse solver (PARDISO) employed; residual norms monitored and confirmed below 1e-8 relative tolerance. No iterative solver divergence observed across all 11 construct configurations. Achieved level exceeds minimum requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed by two independent analysts. Boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions were cross-checked against a documented simulation protocol. Discrepancies identified during review were resolved prior to final runs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model adopted for titanium alloy components consistent with sub-yield loading regime of ASTM F1717 protocol. Contact interactions modeled with penalty-based frictional formulation (mu=0.2). Geometric nonlinearity included to capture large-displacement effects at the screw-rod interface."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from ASTM F136 certified coupon tests for Ti-6Al-4V ELI. Geometric dimensions measured from 11 physical constructs using CMM with traceable calibration. Input uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo propagation; coefficient of variation on stiffness prediction below 4%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from production lots tested across two independent laboratories. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASTM E2935. Lot traceability documented; no outliers excluded without documented justification."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted at a single load level (150 N compressive force with 10 Nm bending moment) per ASTM F1717. Only one test condition was evaluated, preventing assessment of model predictive capability across a range of loading scenarios. This factor does not meet the required level; the deficit is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory context of the standard protocol."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicated ASTM F1717 fixture geometry, constraint locations, and load application points with dimensional fidelity confirmed by overlay of CAD fixture model with test photographs. Clamping torque converted to equivalent preload via thread mechanics analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Predicted construct stiffness compared against experimental mean using normalized error metric. FEA predictions within 8% of experimental mean for all three modelling teams. TOST equivalence testing confirmed predictions statistically equivalent to experimental results at the 5% significance level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and peak interfacial stress are the primary QoIs, directly linked to the clinical performance question of mechanical stability under compressive-bending loading. These QoIs are measurable in both simulation and experiment and are the quantities reported in the regulatory submission."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the ASTM F1717 test protocol that constitutes the regulatory benchmark for spinal fixation device mechanical performance. The validation scenario geometry, materials, and loading are representative of the intended simulation use, supporting the inference that model predictions are credible for the submission context."
    }
  ],
